      "source": "data"
    }
  }
}
</VARIABLES>

<target_variable>accept</target_variable>

<SUMMARY>
A simple logistic fairness model for responder decisions, where the utility is determined by the deviation of the offered share from a fairness benchmark computed from token contributions. Two learnable parameters modulate sensitivity to fairness deviation and baseline bias to predict binary acceptance.
</SUMMARY>

